gomodel:SYNGO_1501  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The authors use synaptosomes prepared from rat cerebellum, to show that 5-HT treatment reduces K+-induced glutamate release, and this inhibition can be relieved with the application of 5-HT1D antagonists.\n\n21/11/2017 Pim\n- In this paper the effect of metabotropic 5HT1 receptors is studied on two phenomena observed in synaptosomal preparations:\n1] glutamate release, presynaptic phenomenon triggered by K+\n2] cGMP production, postsynaptic phenomemon triggered by NMDA/AMPA-R activation caused by 1]\nA. Serotonin and other serotonergic agonists inhibit 1] and 2]\nB. A. is blocked by a 5HT1D antagonist (GR-127935)\nC. Direct activation of NMDA/AMPA-Rs leads to varying efficiency of different Serotonin and other serotonergic agonists on phenomenon 2]. Together with A. this shows that 1] and 2] are functionally related (Glut release causes GlutR activation and cGMP production) and that different 5HT1Rs subtypes regulate 1] and 2]\nD. 5HT1A antagonist ([(+)-WAY100135]) can rescue inhibition of 2] but not of 1] by serotonergic agonists\nConclusion:\n- 5HT1D regulates presynaptic glutamate release\n- 5HT1A regulates postsynaptic cGMP production\n\n- This conclusion on 5HT1D is confirmed in study PMID:16469416 that concludes:\n\"The major finding of our work was that, while the cGMP production evoked by high-micromolar SNAP was insensitive to 5-HT, the cGMP response to NO donor concentrations releasing NO in the low-nanomolar range, was dependent on the release of glutamate and on subsequent activation of glutamate ionotropic receptors/NOS/sGC pathway and could be controlled by activating presynaptic 5-HT receptors of the 5-HT1D subtype.\"\n\n- The 5HT1A-R clearly regulates cGMP production in the postsynapse (NMDA/AMPAR dependent).. Experimental description: 20/11/2017 Pim\n- Tissue was of rat species; \"Adult male rats (Sprague-Dawley, weighing 200-250 g) were housed at constanttemperature ...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4022-8707" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7480-0826" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1212-5623" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5648-066X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2533-9548" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-26" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1501" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

